Off south-western coast of 
Iceland
(
Fig. 1B
). Depth range: 
20 to 221 m
; bottom temperature range: 7.10 to 9.55°C (
Fig. 2B
). The shallowest sample (2557; 
20 m
) was found in north-western fjords. The easternmost sample (2827; 
44 m
) contains the highest number of pectinariid specimens found in any BIOICE sample (770; 96.5%)). Water mass/es: MNAW.

Finally, SEM micrographs also show circular areas under the parapodia with segmentary arrangement (
Fig. 16B
); these are likely nephridial or glandular and may have a role in tube building, although this should be confirmed in future morphological studies.
